Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, dry bread stuffing mix, eggs, water and onion. Mix thoroughly. Shape into 2 small loaves, or 1 large loaf. Put into a 9x13 inch baking dish and cover with pasta sauce. Bake, uncovered, in the preheated oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.